Class TVMRetValue

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AutoCloseable

    @Namespace(value="tvm::runtime")
 @Properties(inherit=tvm_runtime.class)
public class TVMRetValue
extends TVMPODRetValue
    \brief Return Value container, Unlike TVMArgValue, which only holds reference and do not delete the underlying container during destruction. TVMRetValue holds value and will manage the underlying containers when it stores a complicated data type.

      • MoveToCHost

        public void MoveToCHost(TVMValue ret_value,
                        IntPointer ret_type_code)
        \brief Move the value back to front-end via C API. This marks the current container as null. The managed resources are moved to the front-end. The front end should take charge in managing them.
        Parameters:
        ret_value - The return value.
        ret_type_code - The return type code.
